text: Pryse Pryse (1815–1855), also known as Pryse Loveden, was a British Liberal politician. He served as MP for Cardigan Boroughs from 1849 until his death in 1855. Pryse's father, Pryse Pryse (1774–1849) had served as MP for Cardigan Boroughs for over thirty years. He died at an early age of 40 in 1855. ==References== Category:1815 births Category:1855 deaths Category:UK MPs 1852–1857 Category:Liberal Party (UK) MPs for Welsh constituencies Category:People educated at Eton College
